-- Vietnam Stock Movers: Cotec Construction, Phu Nhuan Jewelry
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-04-09T07:36:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-09/vietnam-stock-movers-cotec-construction-phu-nhuan-jewelry.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Vietnam trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 2:15 p.m. local-time close
in Ho Chi Minh City. The  VN Index (VNINDEX) , the benchmark measure of the
Ho Chi Minh City Stock Exchange, rose 0.7 percent to 450.73.  Cotec Construction Joint-Stock Co. (CTD)  , a builder of
roads and housing, climbed 2.4 percent to 38,500 dong, the
biggest advance since March 19. The company will pay a dividend
of 2,000 dong a share on May 16, it said in a statement on the
exchange’s website.  Phu Nhuan Jewelry Joint-Stock Co. (PNJ)  , Vietnam’s only
listed jewelry manufacturer, gained 2.1 percent to 39,800 dong,
the highest close since March 15. Spot gold advanced as much as
0.8 percent to $1,648.80 an ounce and traded at $1,643.63 at
2:05 p.m. Singapore time.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
